description:
Lodging with Lions - Episode 2 | Wildlife Documentary

Watch 'Lodging with Lions - Episode 1' here: https://youtu.be/SmdmgWg54G0

The volunteers participate in an exciting game capture mission. Once the boma is completed, the helicopter drives wildebeest into the funnel and the impalas get caught up in the nets. The volunteers are overwhelmed by the capture process as it’s a hands on job to control the impalas. Two intern researchers observe how lions react to spices and find out that catnip really does have a euphoric reaction.
The volunteers walk with elephants and marvel at their size in real life. We learn about the cubs' feeding habits. A devastating poaching incident is discovered during a snare sweep. And a bushfire runs wild as the volunteers fight to control it.

There’s a place in Africa where you can walk with lions. Where you can be part of the pride. And hundreds of volunteers have a chance to do just that!
They’ve come from all over the world to work in this unique conservation program…to see more lions hunting free in the wilds of Africa and to engage with them like no one else on earth! There’s never a dull moment at Antelope Park.
